-- Balda, BMW, Daimler, Hochtief, Hugo Boss May Move: German Equity Preview
-- B y   A l e x i s   X y d i a s
-- 2010-10-15T06:37:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/balda-bmw-daimler-hochtief-hugo-boss-may-move-german-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Germany. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  The benchmark DAX index rose 0.3 percent to 6,455.27
yesterday, heading for a 2.6 percent gain this week.       Balda AG  (BAF GY): The manufacturer of plastic components
lowered its 2010 forecast, saying it will fall “clearly short”
of the forecast earnings before interest and taxes of about 2.5
million euros ($3.5 million). Earnings before interest and taxes
are likely to be “negative in the single-digit range,” the
company said in a statement. The shares lost 3.7 percent to 6.74
euros.       Bayerische Motoren Werke AG  (BMW GY): Citigroup Inc. raised
its price estimate for the carmaker’s shares to 58 euros from 52
euros, citing the prospects of a “bumper reporting season for
German auto companies.” The brokerage raised its forecast for
 Daimler AG  (DAI GY) to 51 euros from 47 euros. BMW’s shares lost
0.1 percent to 50 euros. Daimler fell 1.1 percent to 47.40
euros.  Hochtief AG  (HOT GY): The board of Actividades de
Construccion y Servicios SA will meet today to call an
extraordinary shareholders’ meeting for the approval of a
capital increase for its planned takeover of Hochtief, Expansion
reported, without saying where it got the information. Shares in
the German builder were little changed at 63.07 euros.  Hugo Boss AG  (BOS3 GY): The clothing retailer was cut to
“hold” from “buy” at Deutsche Bank AG. The shares rose 4.7
percent to 46.12 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Alexis Xydias in London at 
 axydias@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at 
 merritt1@bloomberg.net . 